    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop the<strong> baby plum tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>fennel seeds</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> and grind\u00a0(or chop if you don't have a pestle and mortar) to a fine powder</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-and-fennel-linguine/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with\u00a02 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halved tomatoes</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> ground fennel seeds</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-and-fennel-linguine/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Stir through the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-and-fennel-linguine/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the\u00a0<strong>linguine</strong>\u00a0to a pot of plenty of\u00a0<strong>boiled water\u00a0</strong>with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong>\u00a0and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> </strong>linguine\u00a0for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the\u00a0<strong>cooked</strong> <strong>linguine </strong>and return to the pot, reserving a cup of the<strong>\u00a0starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-and-fennel-linguine/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes are fragrant, add the<strong> tomato stock</strong> and<strong> crab meat</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until thickened to\u00a0a pasta sauce-like consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>fiery tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-and-fennel-linguine/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel the <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> until you end up with a pile of cheese shavings</p><p>Grate any <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-and-fennel-linguine/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained linguine</strong> to the fiery tomato sauce and gently stir together</p><p>Cook for 1 min further until the sauce begins to stick to the pasta \u2013 this is your<strong> fiery tomato, crab & fennel linguine</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy cooking water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-and-fennel-linguine/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> fiery tomato, crab & fennel linguine</strong> topped with <strong>chopped basil</strong> and<strong> Italian hard cheese shavings</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and drizzle with some <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
